            <h2>Filed under 'drm'</h2>
                

    



<h3 class="date"><a href="/2006/mar/27/">&#x27a0;</a> March 27, 2006</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    
    <div class="well" id="nextgen_dvds_blurry_picture" >

        
        <a name="002344"></a>
        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://www.businessweek.com/technology/content/mar2006/tc20060327_546762.htm">Next-Gen DVDs&#39; Blurry Picture</a></h4>

        

        <p>BusinessWeek article on the troubles facing early adopters of HD-DVD &amp; Blu-Ray.  I reckon Comcast &amp; DirecTv are going to win the battle to bring High Def movies into peoples&#8217; homes.  The days of shiny discs are drawing to a close.</p>

        <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span10">
                
