<h3 class="date"><a href="/2005/nov/18/">&#x27a0;</a> November 18, 2005</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    
    <div class="well" id="boing_boing_itunes_creates_a_s" >

        
        <a name="002122"></a>
        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://www.boingboing.net/2005/11/18/itunes_creates_a_sec.html">Boing Boing: iTunes creates a security hole?</a></h4>

        

        <p>*Jawdroppingly* idiotic rant from Cory, trying to draw anti-DRM points from a completely non-DRM-related security flaw in iTunes.  Is it my imagination, or is his signal to ranting-clueless-fuckwit ratio dropping of late?</p>

